<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-07T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-07T03:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.001/356: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-07T17:00:00+09:00">October 7, 1938—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 7—6:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>651. Department’s telegram No. 346, October 6, 7 p.m.,<note n="88" xml:id="d81fn88">Not printed.</note> American rights in China. Note
                            with approved changes was delivered at the Foreign Office this
                                afternoon.<note n="89" xml:id="d81fn89">Dated October 6, <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_785"><hi rend="italic">Foreign
                                        Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 785</ref>.</note> Copy will be sent tomorrow to
                            Shanghai by registered mail.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>